A 58-year-old taxi boss was shot dead by two men at a taxi rank in Rooderpoort. The taxi boss was the chairperson of Dobsonville, Rooderpoort, Leratong, and Johannesburg Taxi Association (DORLJOTA). “One suspect is believed to be a police official attached to JHB Central LCRC,” Police spokesperson Captain Tinyiko Mathebula said. It's alleged that the taxi boss was at a taxi rank when the two suspects approached him and started firing shots at him. Mathebula said the deceased was shot ten times.  He said the the suspects drove off and were allegedly followed by one taxi driver, who then alerted the police of their whereabouts. The police cornered the suspects in Soweto, Protea Glen and arrested them. Motive of the murder is not yet known. 